<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="612" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="15.[1443,2650,1120,1744]" pageId="15" pageNumber="612">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1444,1800,1518,1547]" pageId="15" pageNumber="612">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. The Congolese Brushfurred Rat has recently been captured in primary forest, suggesting it not very rare and probably of Least Concern, but additional data on basic ecology and abundance are needed to clarify its conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
